description:
• Reaches net zero by 2050.
  • Electrified heating. Consumers willing to change behaviour. High energy efficiency. High demand side flexibility.

• Reaches net zero by 2050.
  • Hydrogen for heating. Consumers less inclined to change behaviour. Lower energy efficiency. Supply side flexibility.

• Reaches net zero by 2047.
  • Significant lifestyle change. Mixture of hydrogen and electrification for heating.

• Does not reach net zero by 2050.
  • Minimal behaviour change. Decarbonisation in power and transport but not heat.
